From: Nuno Felicio < nuno.felicio@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 22 Dec 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] phy: rockchip: Fix missing Kconfig dependencies for samsung-dcphy

The PHY_ROCKCHIP_SAMSUNG_DCPHY driver uses V4L2 subdev APIs including
v4l2_subdev->entity member which only exists when CONFIG_MEDIA_CONTROLLER
is enabled. Without proper Kconfig dependencies, disabling CONFIG_MEDIA_SUPPORT
causes a build failure:

  error: 'struct v4l2_subdev' has no member named 'entity'

Add the missing dependencies to match similar drivers like
PHY_ROCKCHIP_CSI2_DPHY and PHY_ROCKCHIP_MIPI_RX which correctly declare
their VIDEO_DEV dependency and select VIDEO_V4L2_SUBDEV_API.

Signed-off-by: Nuno Felicio < nuno.felicio@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/phy/rockchip/Kconfig | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/phy/rockchip/Kconfig b/drivers/phy/rockchip/Kconfig
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/drivers/phy/rockchip/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/phy/rockchip/Kconfig
@@ -131,8 +131,11 @@ config PHY_ROCKCHIP_PCIE
 
 config PHY_ROCKCHIP_SAMSUNG_DCPHY
 	tristate "Rockchip Samsung MIPI DCPHY driver"
+	depends on VIDEO_DEV
 	depends on (ARCH_ROCKCHIP || COMPILE_TEST) && OF
 	select GENERIC_PHY
 	select GENERIC_PHY_MIPI_DPHY
+	select VIDEO_V4L2_SUBDEV_API
+	select V4L2_FWNODE
 	help
 	  Enable this to support the Rockchip MIPI DCPHY with
